&gt; - IBM's VM resolver uses TCP for all queries.

This is incorrect.  The VM resolver can be configured to use either UDP or 
TCP to connect to a name server.  The nameserver does, however, use TCP in 
all transactions with other nameservers.

For trivial queries, it probably would be nice if the nameserver used UDP to 
connect to other nameservers.

Mike Hojnowski
TCPIP Grunt
Cornell University
